techmeme.title: GitHub CEO Thomas Dohmke says he is leaving to "become a startup founder again"; memo: Microsoft is opting not to directly replace the position (Ina Fried/Axios)
Amazon's Kuiper launches 24 satellites via SpaceX's Falcon 9 after four launch attempts were delayed by weather issues, taking its total to 102 in orbit (Annie Palmer/CNBC)
The EU Commission approves Prosus' €4.1B takeover of Just Eat Takeaway in a bid to create a "European tech champion" to rival DoorDash, which acquired Deliveroo (Financial Times)
The CSA releases Matter 1.4.2 to improve reliability, stability, and cross-platform coordination, like Wi-Fi-only commissioning to lose its Bluetooth dependency (Jennifer Pattison Tuohy/The Verge)
Tahoe Therapeutics, which is building AI models of living cells, raised $30M led by Amplify Partners at a $120M valuation, taking its total funding to $42M (Alex Knapp/Forbes)
